{"type":"message","id":"579dbaa2","parentId":"75df7827","timestamp":"2026-02-17T22:11:55.500Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"exec_1771366315431_80","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/home/franklinbaldo/.openclaw/agents/aparicio/workspace/skills/alfarrabios-publisher/scripts/make_cover.py*"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":46,"aggregated":"/home/franklinbaldo/.openclaw/agents/aparicio/workspace/skills/alfarrabios-publisher/scripts/make_cover.py*","cwd":"/home/franklinbaldo/.openclaw/agents/aparicio/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771366315490}}
{"type":"message","id":"3a84aab2","parentId":"579dbaa2","timestamp":"2026-02-17T22:12:02.035Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reading the Script's Intent**\n\nI've confirmed the script's existence and ability to run. Now, my focus is shifting towards deciphering its operational parameters. I intend to thoroughly examine its structure, paying close attention to its arguments and the intended output location. This will help me grasp how it operates.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771366322018_82","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/franklinbaldo/.openclaw/agents/aparicio/workspace/skills/alfarrabios-publisher/scripts/make_cover.py"},"thoughtSignature":"CiQBjz1rX28dOQSQ9+yW4XUI7cjHJq3exD+TxoCU/WteSqFzaAUKaAGPPWtfLRkmwxIj1+fOIK+lSjhNOmVKrH0ntd/4xU1uLCCQtgzSSxaTOSvSQhGd9OB/Jy3k3ZM/xsbnIbtV0pMra5HprMkTCE3oSyWbvX7Ob9+maXD50O4j77oODl/xZgUgICs+H0dACj4Bjz1rXy2cb1ufKVfCNnRZ5ZHHdNcV4YLBMOebITtomOPsq/mc7LSqeCOhM+Ma2mXqgEdinoEZk1l8zcPgIQ=="}],"api":"google-gemini-cli","provider":"google-gemini-cli","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":3047,"output":66,"cacheRead":5442,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8555,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771366315500}}
{"type":"message","id":"72828b03","parentId":"3a84aab2","timestamp":"2026-02-17T22:12:02.087Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771366322018_82","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Generate a mandatory cover image for a blog post using Nano Banana, then crop/resize to 1200x630.\n\nUsage:\n  python3 skills/alfarrabios-publisher/scripts/make_cover.py \\\n    --repo /path/to/adibaldo.github.io \\\n    --slug o-cheiro-do-cafe-na-varanda \\\n    --prompt \"cafe na varanda...\"\n\nNotes:\n- Requires: uv, GEMINI_API_KEY (Nano Banana), Pillow installed.\n- Set NANO_BANANA_SCRIPT env var to override the default path.\n- Output:\n  <repo>/src/content/blog/images/<slug>-cover.png\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport os\nimport subprocess\nimport sys\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nfrom PIL import Image\n\n_DEFAULT_NANO_BANANA = (\n    \"/home/franklinbaldo/.openclaw/agents/aparicio/workspace/scripts/generate_image_flash.py\"\n)\nNANO_BANANA_SCRIPT = Path(os.environ.get(\"NANO_BANANA_SCRIPT\", _DEFAULT_NANO_BANANA))\n\n\ndef crop_to_1200x630(in_path: Path, out_path: Path) -> None:\n    im = Image.open(in_path).convert(\"RGB\")\n    w, h = im.size\n    target_ratio = 1200 / 630\n    cur_ratio = w / h\n    if cur_ratio > target_ratio:\n        new_w = int(h * target_ratio)\n        left = (w - new_w) // 2\n        im = im.crop((left, 0, left + new_w, h))\n    else:\n        new_h = int(w / target_ratio)\n        top = (h - new_h) // 2\n        im = im.crop((0, top, w, top + new_h))\n    im = im.resize((1200, 630), Image.LANCZOS)\n    out_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n    im.save(out_path, format=\"PNG\", optimize=True)\n\n\ndef main() -> int:\n    ap = argparse.ArgumentParser()\n    ap.add_argument(\"--repo\", required=True)\n    ap.add_argument(\"--slug\", required=True)\n    ap.add_argument(\"--prompt\", required=True)\n    ap.add_argument(\"--keep-raw\", action=\"store_true\")\n    args = ap.parse_args()\n\n    repo = Path(args.repo)\n\n    if not NANO_BANANA_SCRIPT.exists():\n        print(\n            f\"ERROR: Nano Banana script not found at {NANO_BANANA_SCRIPT}\\n\"\n            \"Set NANO_BANANA_SCRIPT env var to the correct path.\",\n            file=sys.stderr,\n        )\n        return 1\n\n    raw = repo / \"src/content/blog/images\" / f\"{args.slug}-cover_raw.png\"\n    final = repo / \"src/content/blog/images\" / f\"{args.slug}-cover.png\"\n\n    cmd = [\n        \"uv\",\n        \"run\",\n        str(NANO_BANANA_SCRIPT),\n        \"--prompt\",\n        args.prompt,\n        \"--filename\",\n        str(raw),\n        \"--resolution\",\n        \"2K\",\n    ]\n    subprocess.run(cmd, check=True)\n\n    crop_to_1200x630(raw, final)\n\n    if not args.keep_raw and raw.exists():\n        raw.unlink()\n\n    print(f\"Wrote: {final}\")\n    return 0\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    raise SystemExit(main())\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771366322076}}
{"type":"message","id":"ef3dbf68","parentId":"72828b03","timestamp":"2026-02-17T22:12:10.951Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Deciding Arguments for Execution**\n\nI've got the script, `make_cover.py`, ready to go. Now, the key is defining those arguments. For the `repo`, I'm going with `/home/franklinbaldo/.openclaw/agents/aparicio/workspace/franklinbaldo.github.io/`.  The `slug` is still open, I'm thinking about it now.\n\n\n**Refining Argument Strategies**\n\nI'm zeroing in on the arguments for `make_cover.py`. The `repo` is set, and I've locked in the `slug`. Now, the `prompt` is evolving: I'm aiming for an abstract, digital art style. Before running the script though, I will update the frontmatter of `pontifex-novel-architecture-semantic-probing.md` with the new description, tags, and `heroImage` information.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"edit_1771366330931_85","name":"edit","arguments":{"oldText":"---\nauthor: franklin\ndate: 2024-07-12\ntitle: \"Pontifex: A Novel Architecture for Semantic Probing\"\n---","newText":"---\nauthor: franklin\ndate: 2024-07-12\ntitle: \"Pontifex: A Novel Architecture for Semantic Probing\"\ndescription: \"Introducing Pontifex: a novel architecture for semantic probing that unifies byte-level occlusion with bilateral semantic comparison across multiple embedding spaces.\"\ntags: [\"artificial intelligence\", \"research\", \"interpretability\", \"semantic probing\"]\nheroImage: ./images/pontifex-novel-architecture-semantic-probing-cover.png\nheroImageAlt: \"Abstract geometric representation of neural network layers converging with glowing data streams.\"\n---","file_path":"/home/franklinbaldo/.openclaw/agents/aparicio/workspace/franklinbaldo.github.io/src/content/blog/pontifex-novel-architecture-semantic-probing.md"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-gemini-cli","provider":"google-gemini-cli","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":6676,"output":543,"cacheRead":2824,"cacheWrit