ss-lingual and cross-modal benchmarks, aligning diverse embeddings to reveal shared concepts. We discuss how Pontifex’s cross-space agreement mechanism yields more robust and language-agnostic interpretability, and we outline future directions for extending this approach to multimodal convergence and unsupervised hypothesis generation of semantic features.\n   8 \n     ...","firstChangedLine":5},"isError":false,"timestamp":1771366330978}}
